  "doc_id": "12520",
  "text": "Visual analog scale score for energy and activity A visual analog scale (VAS) is a widely used, subjective, unidimensional questionnaire. Energy and activity levels of the subjects were measured using a VAS on day 1 (pretreatment) and after 5 and 10 days of treatment. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Subjects were instructed to mark on the line how they were feeling at the moment. The total line length was 100 mm. Left-most marks indicated the highest levels of the parameter (100), while right-most marks indicated the lowest levels (0). The distance of each mark was measured in millimeters from the right end of the line. The measurement for each parameter on days 5 and 10 was subtracted from the day 1 preingestion baseline measurement to give an indication of improvement.",
